WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.952 --> 00:00:29.538
Army Rangers have a proud history.

2
00:00:29.747 --> 00:00:33.876
Since the 1700s, Rangers have led
the way in every major confrontation

3
00:00:33.959 --> 00:00:36.920
in which the United States
has been involved.

4
00:00:37.004 --> 00:00:41.342
You, men, are a credit to that fine heritage,
and I'm sorry to see you go.

5
00:00:42.016 --> 00:00:45.429
But you've served your country well,
and you've displayed the ability to fight on

6
00:00:45.512 --> 00:00:47.765
to the Ranger objective
and complete its mission:

7
00:00:48.483 --> 00:00:52.895
never leaving behind a fallen comrade
no matter what the odds or the enemy.

8
00:00:52.978 --> 00:00:54.605
I thank you.

9
00:00:54.688 --> 00:00:56.982
America thanks you.

10
00:00:57.024 --> 00:00:59.789
And I wish you luck
wherever you go.

11
00:01:00.027 --> 00:01:03.697
And remember.
Rangers lead the way.

12
00:01:12.164 --> 00:01:13.957
- Hi, Tricia.
- Hey.

13
00:01:16.794 --> 00:01:18.629
- Hey, Tricia Poe.
- Hello, Dale.

14
00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:23.090
<i>♪ How do I ♪</i>

15
00:01:23.170 --> 00:01:27.630
<i>♪ Get through one night
without you ♪</i>

16
00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:31.470
<i>♪ If I had to live
without you ♪</i>

17
00:01:31.550 --> 00:01:34.770
<i>♪ What kind of life
would that be ♪</i>

18
00:01:34.850 --> 00:01:38.310
<i>♪ Oh, I ♪</i>

19
00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:41.150
<i>♪ I need you in my arms
Need you to hold ♪</i>

20
00:01:41.235 --> 00:01:42.653
- Hummingbird.
- Hi.

21
00:01:42.737 --> 00:01:45.489
<i>♪ - You're my world, my heart and soul ♪</i>
- Look at you.

22
00:01:45.572 --> 00:01:48.492
I'd take a beatin' half my life
to get a piece of that woman.

23
00:01:48.617 --> 00:01:50.486
- How's my baby?
- She's doin' fine.

24
00:01:50.518 --> 00:01:53.760
<i>♪ - Baby, you would take away everything ♪</i>
- Yeah?

25
00:01:53.871 --> 00:01:56.792
<i>♪ - Good in my life ♪</i>
- What? You're kiddin' me!

26
00:01:56.875 --> 00:01:58.877
- What?
- Sweetie?

27
00:01:58.961 --> 00:02:02.058
Hey, shh. Can't you see I'm in
the middle of somethin' here?

28
00:02:02.427 --> 00:02:05.451
<i>♪ - How do I live without you ♪</i>
- What? You... you gonna be Miss Alabama?

29
00:02:05.735 --> 00:02:07.954
Well, that makes your daddy
very proud.

30
00:02:08.030 --> 00:02:14.020
<i>♪ Oh, I know
How do I breathe without you ♪</i>

31
00:02:14.110 --> 00:02:16.020
<i>♪ If you ever go ♪</i>

32
00:02:16.312 --> 00:02:19.823
Tricia Poe!
You little angel, you.

33
00:02:20.206 --> 00:02:22.276
Hey, how about joinin' me
and the boys for a cold one?

34
00:02:22.359 --> 00:02:25.195
- Huh, darlin'?
- No, thanks.

35
00:02:25.279 --> 00:02:27.197
Who's your
captain Huckleberry here?

36
00:02:27.281 --> 00:02:30.576
-You know this gentleman, honey?
- He's a regular.

37
00:02:30.659 --> 00:02:34.913
Yeah, I'm a regular.
Huh. Regular hound dog.

38
00:02:37.499 --> 00:02:39.714
This is a special occasion,
and if you don't mind,

39
00:02:39.714 --> 00:02:41.829
I'd like to spend it
dancin' with my wife.

40
00:02:42.102 --> 00:02:46.425
Tell you what, soldier Dick. Why don't
you go buy me and my buddies a round?

41
00:02:46.771 --> 00:02:49.511
Hey, Cameron, no.
It ain't worth it.

42
00:02:49.595 --> 00:02:53.932
Hey. Come on, daddy,
let's dance.

43
00:02:54.787 --> 00:02:56.185
Oh, chickenshit!

44
00:02:56.268 --> 00:03:00.267
'Cause of pussies like you,
we lost Vietnam. I'll tell ya that.

45
00:03:00.406 --> 00:03:03.442
- We don't need trouble.
- Oh, you should be so proud.

46
00:03:04.994 --> 00:03:07.046
You know, for a second there
you were that guy again.

47
00:03:08.864 --> 00:03:10.240
I know it.

48
00:03:12.084 --> 00:03:16.015
Well, I was hopin' maybe the army
would make that guy grow up.

49
00:03:16.838 --> 00:03:18.402
Well...

50
00:03:18.666 --> 00:03:21.882
- He has.
<i>♪ - Then tell me now ♪</i>

51
00:03:21.940 --> 00:03:26.210
<i>♪ How do I live
without you ♪</i>

52
00:03:26.390 --> 00:03:29.170
<i>♪ I want to know ♪</i>

53
00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:33.510
<i>♪ How do I breathe
without you ♪</i>

54
00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:37.140
<i>♪ If you ever go ♪</i>

55
00:03:46.068 --> 00:03:47.987
Hey, Gomer!

56
00:03:48.070 --> 00:03:51.740
Thought you might need a little help
escortin' your old lady home.

57
00:03:55.703 --> 00:03:58.330
Cameron, let's go home.
Just get in the car.

58
00:03:58.414 --> 00:04:01.166
- Come on.
- Cameron!

59
00:04:02.167 --> 00:04:03.627
Cameron, get in the car!

60
00:04:09.383 --> 00:04:12.136
Dale! Dale!

61
00:04:25.107 --> 00:04:27.109
Take this,
you son of a bitch!

62
00:04:41.248 --> 00:04:43.675
Tricia!

63
00:04:44.293 --> 00:04:46.179
Tricia!

64
00:04:51.383 --> 00:04:54.553
God, he's dead.
Cameron, this guy's dead.

65
00:04:57.473 --> 00:05:00.059
Admit the facts,
enter a plea bargain.

66
00:05:00.142 --> 00:05:02.102
I will not plead guilty.

67
00:05:02.186 --> 00:05:04.396
You could get ten years.

68
00:05:07.733 --> 00:05:11.403
Admit to it, you get four.

69
00:05:11.487 --> 00:05:14.031
Serve maybe a year.

70
00:05:14.114 --> 00:05:19.536
Cameron Poe, you have pleaded guilty
to manslaughter in the first degree.

71
00:05:19.620 --> 00:05:22.539
With your military skills,
you are a deadly weapon

72
00:05:22.623 --> 00:05:25.834
and are not subject to the same laws
as other people that are provoked

73
00:05:25.918 --> 00:05:28.420
because you can respond
with deadly force.

74
00:05:28.504 --> 00:05:32.633
It is the order of this court that
you be remanded to a federal penitentiary

75
00:05:32.716 --> 00:05:37.972
where you shall remain incarcerated
for a term not less than... 7 to 10 years.

76
00:05:47.147 --> 00:05:48.878
Hello, pretty girl.

77
00:05:49.066 --> 00:05:52.116
Come, come.
Bring it here. Hey! Hey!

78
00:05:54.613 --> 00:05:59.493
<i>Dearest Tricia, I think of you always.
Your smile, your laugh.</i>

79
00:05:59.618 --> 00:06:03.455
<i>I'm not angry.
The blame's gotta fall on me.</i>

80
00:06:03.497 --> 00:06:07.909
<i>I am, however, torn apart
when I think that I won't be there</i>

81
00:06:07.909 --> 00:06:09.837
<i>to see our child
come into the world</i>

82
00:06:09.962 --> 00:06:12.923
<i>cradled in your arms,
and her first smile.</i>

83
00:06:14.675 --> 00:06:17.011
<i>I got your package.
Those pink coconut things</i>

84
00:06:17.136 --> 00:06:19.471
<i>have made me quite popular.</i>

85
00:06:19.513 --> 00:06:24.435
<i>Met a guy just the other day.
Baby-O. He sure does love 'em.</i>

86
00:06:26.687 --> 00:06:29.982
<i>And now our daughter,
beautiful Casey.</i>

87
00:06:30.024 --> 00:06:32.484
<i>I watch her grow
in the pictures you send.</i>

88
00:06:32.526 --> 00:06:35.321
<i>I showed 'em to Baby-O.
His reaction was simple.</i>

89
00:06:35.362 --> 00:06:37.990
<i>He said "Thank God
she looks like her mama".</i>

90
00:06:38.032 --> 00:06:39.725
<i>I'd have to agree.</i>

91
00:06:40.146 --> 00:06:44.091
<i>It's funny, but here I am in maybe
the worst place on earth, and yet,</i>

92
00:06:44.091 --> 00:06:46.832
<i>somehow, I feel like
the luckiest man alive.</i>

93
00:06:53.672 --> 00:06:58.469
<i>Dear daddy, I started today at
the Little Sunshine Day Care Center.</i>

94
00:06:58.552 --> 00:07:01.472
<i>My teacher is Miss Gordon.
She is nice.</i>

95
00:07:01.555 --> 00:07:04.975
<i>We go to playtime, and we all have
to hold hands when we walk there.</i>

96
00:07:05.059 --> 00:07:08.228
<i>Dear Casey, it was so good
to read your letter.</i>

97
00:07:08.354 --> 00:07:10.314
<i>I'm glad you like your teacher.</i>

98
00:07:10.397 --> 00:07:12.858
<i>We don't exactly have
a playtime like you.</i>

99
00:07:12.983 --> 00:07:17.321
<i>We do go outside, though. But
normally, we don't hold hands.</i>

100
00:07:21.241 --> 00:07:25.037
<i>My wife and I will have
our Margaritas on the yacht.</i>

101
00:07:32.002 --> 00:07:35.214
<i>Dear daddy, today was
my first day at first grade.</i>

102
00:07:35.255 --> 00:07:39.343
<i>I didn't like it. I don't want
to go back tomorrow.</i>

103
00:07:39.426 --> 00:07:43.931
<i>This boy, Scotty Dalton, has
black teeth and calls me names.</i>

104
00:07:44.056 --> 00:07:47.893
<i>Mama says I have to go back.
Tell her not to make me.</i>

105
00:07:47.935 --> 00:07:52.731
<i>Dear Casey, hopefully this finds you
still goin' to the first grade.</i>

106
00:07:52.773 --> 00:07:57.069
<i>School is very important.
Your mama's right.</i>

107
00:07:57.111 --> 00:08:00.280
<i>Now, don't you worry
about little Scotty Dalton.</i>

108
00:08:00.406 --> 00:08:04.201
<i>Sometimes you meet people like that,
but don't let 'em get you down.</i>

109
00:08:08.455 --> 00:08:12.814
<i>Dear daddy,
are you ever comin' home?</i>

110
00:08:13.043 --> 00:08:16.046
<i>Dear Casey,
of course I'm comin' home.</i>

111
00:08:16.130 --> 00:08:19.425
<i>In just a little while longer, and all
the things we missed doin' together,</i>

112
00:08:19.550 --> 00:08:21.552
<i>you can be sure we'll do.</i>

113
00:08:21.635 --> 00:08:26.098
<i>Dear Hummingbird, break out
the fine china, chill the lemonade,</i>

114
00:08:26.140 --> 00:08:28.434
<i>tie a yellow ribbon
'round the old oak tree</i>

115
00:08:28.475 --> 00:08:32.438
<i>'cause this boy's comin' home to
his ladies, comin' home forever.</i>

116
00:08:32.563 --> 00:08:37.067
<i>I just hope I'm not a disappointment
to Casey or to you.</i>

117
00:08:37.870 --> 00:08:39.666
<i>Love, Cameron.</i>

118
00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:43.324
"My daddy is coming home
on July 14th."

119
00:08:43.407 --> 00:08:46.066
"My birthday is July 14th."

120
00:08:46.410 --> 00:08:50.831
"I'm gonna see my daddy for
the first time ever on July 14th."

121
00:08:50.914 --> 00:08:54.626
I can't wait to meet you, honey. Isn't
that the cutest thing you ever heard?

122
00:08:54.752 --> 00:08:56.795
Yeah, man.

123
00:08:58.464 --> 00:09:00.055
Hey, now, what is this?

124
00:09:01.050 --> 00:09:03.061
I can't see my little daughter
on her birthday

125
00:09:03.061 --> 00:09:05.103
without bringin'
her a gift, now can I?

126
00:09:05.304 --> 00:09:07.658
Yeah, man,
but that's a bunny rabbit.

127
00:09:07.765 --> 00:09:10.059
That's all right. I mean,
she'll like it, right? I mean, what?

128
00:09:10.142 --> 00:09:12.416
It's either this
or a tube of toothpaste

129
00:09:12.416 --> 00:09:14.298
and two packs
of Pall Malls at the canteen.

130
00:09:14.298 --> 00:09:18.157
- Now, that's a present.
- I'll remember that on your birthday.

131
00:09:18.157 --> 00:09:20.429
Yeah, you do that, man.

132
00:09:25.991 --> 00:09:29.787
"It having been made to appear to
the United States Parole Commission,"

133
00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:33.749
"Cameron Poe is eligible
to be paroled."

134
00:09:33.832 --> 00:09:37.270
Shit, might be a long time before I see
somethin' like that with my name on it.

135
00:09:44.510 --> 00:09:46.868
You'll get your own date
someday, Baby-O.

136
00:09:47.769 --> 00:09:49.143
I ain't worried about that, man.

137
00:09:49.223 --> 00:09:52.810
Yeah, but like at this new prison you're
goin' to, who's gonna watch your back?

138
00:09:52.893 --> 00:09:56.105
God's got my back.
You know what I'm sayin'?

139
00:09:58.190 --> 00:10:00.288
I'm goin' home, son!

140
00:10:00.526 --> 00:10:03.195
Wait, don't be gettin' all juicy
on me, all right? Get off me.

141
00:10:05.072 --> 00:10:06.806
Step out.

142
00:10:10.327 --> 00:10:13.372
Good-bye. Good night.

143
00:10:22.229 --> 00:10:24.174
The U.S. Marshal Service
annually flies

144
00:10:24.258 --> 00:10:27.511
155,000 prisoners
around the country

145
00:10:27.594 --> 00:10:30.639
for transfers, legal hearings
and medical exams.

146
00:10:30.723 --> 00:10:34.727
As you know, today's flight
is a special one.

147
00:10:34.852 --> 00:10:38.188
We're populating Alabama's
Feltham Penitentiary,

148
00:10:38.272 --> 00:10:41.317
the newest super-max facility
in the system.

149
00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:44.653
This place was designed
to warehouse the worst of the worst.

150
00:10:44.737 --> 00:10:48.574
Now, most of these guys
are lifers, some on death row.

151
00:10:48.657 --> 00:10:52.661
Pure predators,
each and every one of them.

152
00:10:55.205 --> 00:10:58.375
- Hey, lady!
- Lady's a dog in a Walt Disney movie.

153
00:10:58.459 --> 00:11:00.919
My name is Bishop.
Guard Bishop to you.

154
00:11:01.045 --> 00:11:04.548
I gotta be gettin' my shot before
we go gettin' on some airplane, guard Bishop.

155
00:11:04.632 --> 00:11:05.521
What's your name?

156
00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:08.826
Odell. They didn't give me
my shot last night.

157
00:11:08.969 --> 00:11:12.147
Okay, you're diabetic? All
right, your insulin's on board.

158
00:11:12.147 --> 00:11:13.726
We'll give it to you in flight.

159
00:11:14.933 --> 00:11:16.935
- Cameron Poe.
- Yes, ma'am.

160
00:11:17.019 --> 00:11:18.854
You know you're still under full
restraints till you're processed

161
00:11:18.937 --> 00:11:21.065
and released from
your original prison, understand?

162
00:11:21.148 --> 00:11:24.401
Yes, ma'am. As long as I make it home
on time, it makes no never mind.

163
00:11:24.485 --> 00:11:27.279
- It's my daughter's birthday.
- Well, congratulations.

164
00:11:27.363 --> 00:11:31.367
I got locked down three months before
she was born. She ain't never seen me.

165
00:11:31.450 --> 00:11:33.827
- And why not?
- No way was she gonna meet her daddy

166
00:11:33.911 --> 00:11:37.623
in a prison visitor room
surrounded by... homemade cookies and...

167
00:11:37.748 --> 00:11:39.557
and love-starved murderers.

168
00:11:40.334 --> 00:11:41.401
No way.

169
00:11:41.401 --> 00:11:44.766
What you got here is a walking
talking reason to rehabilitate.

170
00:11:48.824 --> 00:11:53.263
So, today let's exemplify
our three operative words:

171
00:11:53.347 --> 00:11:56.558
firm, fair and vigilant.

172
00:11:57.685 --> 00:11:59.439
Now, let's go to work.

173
00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:01.981
We off-load six in Carson City,
the rest are sheeted to Feltham.

174
00:12:02.106 --> 00:12:04.274
Good. Let's go deal
with the DEA boys.

175
00:12:08.529 --> 00:12:10.114
- You know this guy?
- Haven't had the pleasure.

176
00:12:10.197 --> 00:12:13.082
He's a piece of work,
a real piece of work.

177
00:12:14.034 --> 00:12:16.912
Duncan, good to see you.
She sure is beautiful.

178
00:12:16.996 --> 00:12:20.624
Hey, beautiful? Sunsets are beautiful.
Newborn babies are beautiful.

179
00:12:20.708 --> 00:12:22.751
This, this is
fucking spectacular!

180
00:12:22.835 --> 00:12:25.963
Duncan, this is Vince Larkin.
He's overseeing the transpo.

181
00:12:26.046 --> 00:12:29.976
- Vince, Duncan Malloy, DEA.
- Nice to meet ya.

182
00:12:29.976 --> 00:12:33.895
I'm sure we're gonna have a good time
working on this together.

183
00:12:49.153 --> 00:12:50.472
- Hey, Willie.
- Boys!

184
00:12:50.472 --> 00:12:51.437
- How you doin'?
- What's up, chief?

185
00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:52.290
You know each other?

186
00:12:52.290 --> 00:12:53.621
- Vince Larkin.
- Sims, DEA. Good to meet you, Larkin.

187
00:12:53.621 --> 00:12:56.577
This is our file on your man,
Francisco Cindino, son of Eduardo,

188
00:12:56.618 --> 00:12:58.245
prime mover of narcotics
from Colombia.

189
00:12:58.329 --> 00:13:00.675
It's gonna be
an all-star flight.

190
00:13:01.498 --> 00:13:04.084
This kid's a potential fountain of
information about the family business.

191
00:13:04.168 --> 00:13:06.211
- Eleven and a half okay?
- Yeah.

192
00:13:06.295 --> 00:13:08.547
Look at him.
Nice college boy, right?

193
00:13:08.631 --> 00:13:10.591
We interrogated him for months.
He gave up nothing.

194
00:13:10.633 --> 00:13:12.843
This is our last chance
before the FBI gets him.

195
00:13:12.926 --> 00:13:14.970
Over my dead body,
those assholes get the glory.

196
00:13:15.416 --> 00:13:17.389
We pick up Mr. Cindino
in Carson City.

197
00:13:17.473 --> 00:13:20.351
From then until the plane hits Alabama,
we've got two hours to get him to talk.

198
00:13:20.434 --> 00:13:22.353
We got you a seat right next
to him, and he's known to be

199
00:13:22.436 --> 00:13:24.271
somewhat garrulous
in the company of thieves.

200
00:13:24.355 --> 00:13:26.398
Garrulous?
What the fuck is garrulous?

201
00:13:26.482 --> 00:13:30.402
That would be loquacious, verbose,
effusive. How about "chatty"?

202
00:13:30.486 --> 00:13:32.404
What's with dictionary boy here?

203
00:13:32.488 --> 00:13:35.491
Thesaurus boy, I think,
is more appropriate.

204
00:13:35.574 --> 00:13:37.660
- You got your gun?
- Yeah.

205
00:13:37.743 --> 00:13:40.496
- Whoa, whoa. Gun?
- We got rules, gentlemen.

206
00:13:40.579 --> 00:13:43.957
- Yeah. So do we. Our agents go armed.
- No one carries on this flight.

207
00:13:44.041 --> 00:13:46.293
I got a small arsenal
in the belly of the plane.

208
00:13:46.377 --> 00:13:49.254
A pistol in the cockpit
lockbox. That's it.

209
00:13:49.338 --> 00:13:51.256
Other than that, we keep
the plane like a prison.

210
00:13:51.340 --> 00:13:53.342
No weapon
on the aircraft, period.

211
00:13:53.425 --> 00:13:56.011
My man does not get on
that plane without his gun.

212
00:13:56.095 --> 00:13:58.514
Then your man
doesn't get on the plane.

213
00:14:01.934 --> 00:14:04.144
Okay, Willie, give it to him.

214
00:14:05.437 --> 00:14:07.439
Give him the gun.

215
00:14:14.113 --> 00:14:16.156
- Avoid eye contact.
- I got it.

216
00:14:16.240 --> 00:14:20.160
- In the pen, it's a sign of aggression.
- Larkin! I got it.

217
00:14:20.244 --> 00:14:22.050
Okay.

218
00:14:24.540 --> 00:14:26.959
<i>Foxtrot Charlie,
we are ready to disembark.</i>

219
00:14:27.042 --> 00:14:29.646
<i>Waiting your go
on separate transfer.</i>

