the plane and he didn't do it.

803
00:57:51.680 --> 00:57:54.308
And I was hoping
you could...

804
00:57:54.391 --> 00:57:57.978
maybe help me
figure out... why.

805
00:57:58.205 --> 00:58:01.095
That would make two of us.
I don't know.

806
00:58:01.323 --> 00:58:03.367
I mean, it's possible,
it's... it's not uncommon

807
00:58:03.492 --> 00:58:07.371
that some parolees actually...
fear their release date.

808
00:58:07.496 --> 00:58:11.125
A certain degree of institutionalization
sets in. Fear of comin' home.

809
00:58:11.208 --> 00:58:12.585
Fear of livin' in society...

810
00:58:12.585 --> 00:58:14.012
- Any of this make sense?
- No, no.

811
00:58:14.236 --> 00:58:17.831
That's not Cameron. I mean, if you...
if you knew him, if you read his letters

812
00:58:17.873 --> 00:58:20.667
or if you talked to him
on the phone, you'd know that...

813
00:58:20.751 --> 00:58:25.005
I mean, he's been waitin' for this day
for eight years. He's not gonna...

814
00:58:27.424 --> 00:58:32.012
I mean, look, he's got this little...
this little girl to come home to.

815
00:58:33.889 --> 00:58:36.183
Wouldn't you...

816
00:58:36.266 --> 00:58:38.352
do the same thing?

817
00:58:41.230 --> 00:58:44.358
