01:07:48.068 --> 01:07:49.928
The last guy who told me
to have patience?

910
01:07:49.928 --> 01:07:52.058
I burned him down,
and bagged his ashes.

911
01:07:52.058 --> 01:07:53.791
Cyrus, it'll be here.

912
01:08:01.173 --> 01:08:04.885
Hey, you stupid sons of bitches!
Jesus Christ!

913
01:08:11.291 --> 01:08:13.635
I hope he likes sand.

914
01:08:13.719 --> 01:08:16.576
Muchacho, run and check out the
tower. Have a look-see, yeah?

915
01:08:16.576 --> 01:08:17.410
All right.

916
01:08:17.445 --> 01:08:18.932
You come with us.

917
01:08:23.353 --> 01:08:25.206
- Let's go. We're gettin' off.
- Boss, I can't.

918
01:08:25.206 --> 01:08:26.142
Yes, you can. Come on!

919
01:08:26.142 --> 01:08:28.492
- You shouldn't move him.
- I'm gettin' him off of this plane.

920
01:08:28.575 --> 01:08:32.579
You... you can't move him.
He's too far along. He could go into shock.

921
01:08:32.663 --> 01:08:34.957
Ah, she's right, Poe.
Go on, man.

922
01:08:35.440 --> 01:08:37.618
I'm not leavin'
without you, or you.

923
01:08:37.701 --> 01:08:40.662
Ah, listen. Here we go.
Ranger boy.

924
01:08:40.746 --> 01:08:44.041
- Right.
- Goddamn it, Poe!

925
01:08:44.124 --> 01:08:46.710
Man, it's time to fight,
fuck or hit the fence.

926
01:08:46.793 --> 01:08:49.254
- I suggest you hit the fence.
- He's right.

927
01:08:49.765 --> 01:08:51.185
Just go.

928
01:08:51.598 --> 01:08:55.177
All right. Here's how it's gonna play.
I'm gonna get you that needle.

929
01:08:55.260 --> 01:08:57.971
Whatever you say, man.
Just do what you gotta do.

930
01:08:58.055 --> 01:08:59.309
Fuck.

931
01:08:59.523 --> 01:09:02.318
All right, you just hang on.
Don't die on me.

932
01:09:03.071 --> 01:09:07.972
<i>♪ Swing low, sweet chariot ♪</i>

933
01:09:08.180 --> 01:09:11.200
<i>♪ Comin' for
to carry me home ♪</i>

934
01:09:11.435 --> 01:09:15.188
Oh, no. What the hell
you think you're doin'?

935
01:09:15.230 --> 01:09:18.025
- It's time to off the pigs.
- You can't do that.

936
01:09:18.066 --> 01:09:21.069
- Tell me why.
- They're hostages. We need 'em.

937
01:09:21.194 --> 01:09:25.949
- But why the fuck you care?
- Hey, man, come on.

938
01:09:26.033 --> 01:09:30.037
I can't think of a thing
I'd like... better

939
01:09:30.120 --> 01:09:34.541
than to put a bullet in the brain base
of every one of these fuckers!

940
01:09:34.624 --> 01:09:38.587
But the fact of the matter is,
how well you know this Cindino?

941
01:09:38.712 --> 01:09:41.798
I mean, I don't know him that
well myself. Just what I read.

942
01:09:41.923 --> 01:09:43.779
Like how he firebombed
that senator's yacht

943
01:09:43.779 --> 01:09:45.906
with two of his own cousins
on board.

944
01:09:45.906 --> 01:09:47.112
So what's your point?

945
01:09:47.196 --> 01:09:49.086
Why would he sweat
about killin' some hired guns

946
01:09:49.086 --> 01:09:50.179
once they'd served his purpose?

947
01:09:50.179 --> 01:09:53.661
- Now think about that.
- What exactly are we discussing here?

948
01:09:53.944 --> 01:09:56.363
Poe don't want me
to off the pigs.

949
01:09:56.646 --> 01:10:00.400
Well, it's not difficult to surmise how
Nathan here feels about killing guards.

950
01:10:00.484 --> 01:10:03.070
And my own proclivities
are, uh...

951
01:10:03.153 --> 01:10:08.075
well-known and, uh,
often-lamented facts of penal lore.

952
01:10:08.217 --> 01:10:11.495
What I'm wonderin' is why you have
any opinion about it at all.

953
01:10:11.578 --> 01:10:14.414
Cyrus, this is your barbecue,
man, and it tastes good.

954
01:10:14.456 --> 01:10:18.635
But I was just sayin' to Mr... Dog
over here, that if it was my barbecue

955
01:10:18.719 --> 01:10:21.027
I'd wait for that
old jumbo jet in the sky

956
01:10:21.027 --> 01:10:22.451
before I start
killin' our only leverage.

957
01:10:22.651 --> 01:10:23.358
Shut the fuck up!

958
01:10:23.358 --> 01:10:25.696
Don't you want to get high
and get laid? No shit!

959
01:10:25.696 --> 01:10:26.694
Oh, fuck this!

960
01:10:26.777 --> 01:10:31.323
Put the gun down.
Put the gun down, Nathan.

961
01:10:31.407 --> 01:10:34.128
Poe's right.
We're goin' to Plan "B".

962
01:10:34.545 --> 01:10:37.112
Gonna get a refuelling truck
and a tractor.

963
01:10:37.237 --> 01:10:39.615
So get back there
and dig the plane out.

964
01:10:56.724 --> 01:11:01.507
No. Yes!

965
01:11:17.194 --> 01:11:20.726
Viking, 'bout time to go
and get that tractor, yeah?

966
01:11:20.726 --> 01:11:22.017
Right.

967
01:11:23.534 --> 01:11:26.286
- I'll get the fuel truck.
- Thanks, Poe.

968
01:11:26.570 --> 01:11:29.122
You've proven to be
a most useful mammal.

969
01:11:29.206 --> 01:11:33.035
"Many hands make light work."
My daddy taught me that.

970
01:11:33.160 --> 01:11:35.662
- You know what my daddy taught me?
- What's that?

971
01:11:35.746 --> 01:11:39.791
- Nothin'.
- Self-educated man.

972
01:11:42.335 --> 01:11:45.514
- Have you found Vince Larkin?
- We're having trouble reaching him, sir.

973
01:11:45.639 --> 01:11:48.350
Of course, you're having trouble
reaching him!

974
01:11:48.475 --> 01:11:53.063
He's off savin' the rain forest
or recycling his sandals or some shit.

975
01:12:27.297 --> 01:12:29.443
Holy shit!

976
01:12:35.939 --> 01:12:39.359
Hey! We got company!

977
01:12:39.401 --> 01:12:41.487
Hey!

978
01:12:41.570 --> 01:12:44.114
We got company!

979
01:12:45.449 --> 01:12:47.328
Go get Cyrus.

980
01:12:48.722 --> 01:12:49.637
Yo, Cyrus!

981
01:12:57.044 --> 01:12:59.087
How long we got
till they get here, Nathan?

982
01:12:59.213 --> 01:13:02.317
Ten, twelve minutes tops.

983
01:13:11.391 --> 01:13:14.853
Hey, what's your name?
Wanna play?

984
01:13:26.490 --> 01:13:28.408
Nice jet.

985
01:13:28.492 --> 01:13:31.745
You can take Cindino and leave
the rest to rot for all I care.

986
01:13:32.354 --> 01:13:37.808
You fire that weapon, 20 pissed-off
prisoners are gonna hear it. Comprendre, esse?

987
01:13:41.163 --> 01:13:44.675
Hooray for the sounds
of fuckin' silence.

988
01:13:44.758 --> 01:13:46.593
Freeze!

989
01:14:05.946 --> 01:14:08.073
- You're Cameron Poe.
- That's right.

990
01:14:08.157 --> 01:14:10.951
- I'm Larkin.
- Hello, Larkin.

991
01:14:11.127 --> 01:14:13.287
- I got your message.
- Where are the troops?

992
01:14:13.570 --> 01:14:16.323
- They'll be here.
- "They'll be here"?

993
01:14:16.634 --> 01:14:18.058
Uh-huh. In a minute.

994
01:14:19.225 --> 01:14:22.996
Listen, Poe...
Can I lower this?

995
01:14:23.238 --> 01:14:25.924
- Go ahead.
- You gonna lower yours?

996
01:14:26.008 --> 01:14:29.136
Sorry, boss, but there's only
two men I trust.

997
01:14:29.219 --> 01:14:31.638
One of them's me.
The other's not you.

998
01:14:33.607 --> 01:14:35.738
So Cindino was running
a drag on everyone.

999
01:14:36.444 --> 01:14:37.446
Yeah.

1000
01:14:37.481 --> 01:14:40.790
If you can't trust a South American
drug lord, who can you trust, huh?

1001
01:14:42.900 --> 01:14:43.888
That was a joke.

1002
01:14:43.888 --> 01:14:47.067
I'm glad you told me.
Now I gotta get back to the plane.

1003
01:14:48.572 --> 01:14:51.533
You're a free man, Poe.
What are you doin'?

1004
01:14:51.658 --> 01:14:54.995
I can't trade a friend's life
for my own, Larkin. That's all.

1005
01:14:55.275 --> 01:14:57.145
You got a friend on board...

1006
01:14:57.989 --> 01:15:01.574
See, I knew I was right
about you. I read your file.

1007
01:15:01.877 --> 01:15:05.422
You're not such a bad guy. Just always
in the wrong place at the wrong time.

1008
01:15:05.506 --> 01:15:07.674
Goodbye... Larkin.

1009
01:15:09.676 --> 01:15:11.805
I spoke to your wife.

1010
01:15:18.268 --> 01:15:20.813
- In person?
- In person.

1011
01:15:21.855 --> 01:15:23.774
And your little girl.

1012
01:15:25.901 --> 01:15:31.258
- You... saw Casey?
- Uh-huh.

1013
01:15:33.450 --> 01:15:36.370
If this thing goes bad, Larkin,
I'm afraid my daughter

1014
01:15:36.411 --> 01:15:39.251
won't... understand.

1015
01:15:39.748 --> 01:15:43.553
If you talk to my wife again,
you tell her...

1016
01:15:44.127 --> 01:15:45.965
I love her.

1017
01:15:47.130 --> 01:15:49.509
She's my hummingbird.

1018
01:15:50.133 --> 01:15:54.660
But... I couldn't leave
a fallen man behind.

1019
01:15:57.307 --> 01:16:00.394
You'll do that for me,
won't you, Larkin?

1020
01:16:00.477 --> 01:16:04.648
Sure I will.
What are you gonna do for me?

1021
01:16:04.731 --> 01:16:07.151
What do you think
I'm gonna do?

1022
01:16:07.234 --> 01:16:09.236
I'm gonna save
the fuckin' day.

1023
01:16:23.584 --> 01:16:27.296
Let's go, gentlemen.
The cavalry is on its way.

1024
01:16:27.421 --> 01:16:30.097
I want this airplane out now.

1025
01:16:31.201 --> 01:16:32.449
Come on, men!

1026
01:16:47.259 --> 01:16:50.544
- About another ten minutes.
- You said ten minutes ten minutes ago.

1027
01:16:54.323 --> 01:16:56.617
Hello, Bob.
Wanna come over for dinner?

1028
01:17:01.497 --> 01:17:04.173
Are you sick?

1029
01:17:04.825 --> 01:17:08.286
- Why do you ask?
- You look sick.

1030
01:17:09.880 --> 01:17:13.342
- I am sick.
- You take medicine?

1031
01:17:13.467 --> 01:17:15.594
There is no medicine
for what I have.

1032
01:17:17.137 --> 01:17:19.932
- Wanna sing?
- Sing?

1033
01:17:20.015 --> 01:17:22.643
Do you know "He's Got
the Whole World in His Hands"?

1034
01:17:23.769 --> 01:17:25.354
Yes, I do.

1035
01:17:25.448 --> 01:17:29.306
<i>♪ He's got the whole world
in His hands ♪</i>

1036
01:17:29.315 --> 01:17:32.096
<i>♪ He's got
the whole wide world ♪</i>

1037
01:17:32.252 --> 01:17:34.212
Come on.

1038
01:17:34.286 --> 01:17:39.199
<i>♪ He's got the whole world
in His hands ♪</i>

1039
01:17:39.308 --> 01:17:43.479
<i>♪ He's got the whole wide world
in His hands ♪</i>

1040
01:17:43.687 --> 01:17:48.066
<i>♪ He's got the whole world
in His hands ♪</i>

1041
01:17:48.275 --> 01:17:52.133
<i>♪ He's got the whole world
in His hands ♪</i>

1042
01:18:10.402 --> 01:18:12.693
It's on the ground. Repeat.
The plane is on the ground.

1043
01:18:12.776 --> 01:18:14.936
But it won't be for long.
Where the hell are ya?

1044
01:18:15.020 --> 01:18:17.105
We're westbound
near the Lerner cutoff.

1045
01:18:48.103 --> 01:18:50.063
Where's Cindino?

1046
01:18:53.275 --> 01:18:55.652
That's my fuckin' plane!

1047
01:19:41.498 --> 01:19:43.417
Cyrus, help me.

1048
01:19:47.254 --> 01:19:50.924
- Looks like you missed your connection.
- We were... We were coming to get you.

1049
01:19:53.969 --> 01:19:55.729
Please.

1050
01:19:56.213 --> 01:19:57.923
- Cy...
- ...onara.

1051
01:19:58.006 --> 01:20:00.425
No!

1052
01:20:38.338 --> 01:20:42.434
- Don't kill me.
- I'm not gonna kill you, old-timer.

1053
01:20:42.559 --> 01:20:44.745
Listen, I need a syringe.

1054
01:20:44.862 --> 01:20:48.199
Oh, no!
Drugs'll end you, son.

1055
01:20:48.282 --> 01:20:50.367
Is there a first aid kit
around here?

1056
01:20:50.451 --> 01:20:53.320
Well, there might be one in
the fire truck over on the boneyard.

1057
01:20:53.404 --> 01:20:57.887
All right, thanks. You just stay here
and don't panic.

1058
01:20:57.950 --> 01:21:01.078
That's easy for you to say.
You don't gotta take a piss.

1059
01:21:15.810 --> 01:21:17.377
- Let's get it on.
- Oh, yeah, that's nice.

1060
01:21:17.899 --> 01:21:18.841
Lock and load!

1061
01:21:22.975 --> 01:21:26.604
Considering my audience, I'm gonna
make this very quick, very simple.

1062
01:21:26.687 --> 01:21:30.482
This is the boneyard.
This is the hangar.

1063
01:21:30.608 --> 01:21:32.484
This is our plane.

1064
01:21:32.610 --> 01:21:36.363
- What's that?
- That's a rock.

1065
01:21:36.849 --> 01:21:37.894
Okay.

1066
01:21:38.524 --> 01:21:41.902
The convoy will enter
the boneyard through here.

1067
01:21:41.985 --> 01:21:45.405
Initially, we take out the first car.
Then we take out the last,

1068
01:21:45.489 --> 01:21:48.325
creating a trap,
an airtight cage

1069
01:21:48.408 --> 01:21:51.587
filled with lots and lots
of dead people.

1070
01:21:51.670 --> 01:21:54.428
Nathan, set everybody
in their position, yeah?

1071
01:21:56.404 --> 01:21:58.734
Bring me
those propane tanks.

1072
01:22:01.013 --> 01:22:03.161
Whoo, go girl.

1073
01:22:04.224 --> 01:22:07.353
Let's go, let's go. Get 'em in there.
if they give you any trouble, kill 'em.

1074
01:22:10.564 --> 01:22:12.250
What can I do?

1075
01:22:12.483 --> 01:22:15.694
Take this.
Go into the boneyard, yeah?

1076
01:22:15.819 --> 01:22:18.414
Anybody gets through,
you scratch their eyes out.

1077
01:22:18.414 --> 01:22:20.010
You got it.

1078
01:23:11.658 --> 01:23:14.329
Come on, little piggy.

1079
01:23:32.021 --> 01:23:35.065
Closer. Closer. Closer.

1080
01:23:42.114 --> 01:23:44.303
Christ.
They'll be slaughtered.

1081
01:23:47.261 --> 01:23:50.264
This is Larkin.
Tell your men to fall back!

1082
01:23:50.447 --> 01:23:52.177
Now.

1083
01:24:23.038 --> 01:24:26.292
Come on, you stinking
piece-of-shit car!

1084
01:24:30.520 --> 01:24:34.483
- What are you gonna do?
- What you doin', man?

1085
01:24:35.668 --> 01:24:37.836
Well, Baby-O...

1086
01:24:37.920 --> 01:24:41.507
it's not exactly Mai tais
and Yahtzee out here, but...

1087
01:24:42.850 --> 01:24:44.694
let's do it!

1088
01:24:56.522 --> 01:24:59.191
Gonna see
what happens now, bitch!

1089
01:24:59.316 --> 01:25:00.818
Bishop.

1090
01:25:13.155 --> 01:25:16.033
- Get the fuck off me!
- I'm gonna bust your ass!

1091
01:25:18.702 --> 01:25:21.705
Leave her alone, man!

1092
01:25:34.092 --> 01:25:35.861
Get behind the truck!

1093
01:25:35.986 --> 01:25:37.780
Get behind the truck!

1094
01:25:56.757 --> 01:26:00.529
When you wake up, Bishop,
I'll be Johnny 24.

1095
01:26:00.685 --> 01:26:02.066
You wanna fight somebody?

1096
01:26:20.230 --> 01:26:24.652
Don't treat... women...
like... that!

1097
01:26:27.571 --> 01:26:29.114
Aw, shit!

1098
01:26:33.202 --> 01:26:34.620
Whoa! Whoa!

1099
01:26:36.864 --> 01:26:39.512
Get back to the plane!

1100
01:26:42.327 --> 01:26:43.829
Oh, my God!

1101
01:26:59.028 --> 01:27:00.888
Okay!

1102
01:27:02.356 --> 01:27:05.651
You might better
get yourself a seat now.

1103
01:27:10.531 --> 01:27:14.451
- Come on.
- Oh, shit! We're in.

1104
01:27:19.581 --> 01:27:21.834
Just take it and let's go.
Get ready to move.

1105
01:27:28.465 --> 01:27:30.926
We're tied up!

1106
01:27:47.776 --> 01:27:50.362
- Now, come on!
- Okay, I'm comin'.

1107
01:27:53.616 --> 01:27:56.952
- Go for the tires!
- Fuck the tires! I'm goin' for the pilot!

1108
01:28:09.498 --> 01:28:11.416
Isn't that your car, Malloy?

1109
01:28:11.853 --> 01:28:14.353
Couldn't be.
I left mine at the office.

1110
01:28:17.806 --> 01:28:20.976
On any other day,
that might seem strange.

1111
01:28:32.988 --> 01:28:36.450
Gotta get her nose up!

1112
01:29:05.488 --> 01:29:07.682
Fuckers! Come on!

1113
01:29:08.440 --> 01:29:11.129
When this is over,
so are you, you little prick!

1114
01:29:11.129 --> 01:29:11.614
Okay.

1115
01:29:20.411 --> 01:29:22.371
Bye-bye, Bob, bye-bye.

1116
01:29:30.513 --> 01:29:31.847
Go, girl!

1117
01:29:32.046 --> 01:29:34.344
<i>♪ Sweet home Alabama ♪</i>

1118
01:29:34.550 --> 01:29:36.427
All right!

1119
01:29:36.955 --> 01:29:39.358
<i>♪ Where the skies
are so blue ♪</i>

1120
01:29:39.563 --> 01:29:41.999
Define irony.

1121
01:29:42.308 --> 01:29:44.476
Bunch of idiots
dancing on a plane

1122
01:29:44.560 --> 01:29:49.690
to a song made famous by a band
that died in a plane crash.

1123
01:30:22.514 --> 01:30:26.936
Someone alerted the authorities
at Carson City.

1124
01:30:27.019 --> 01:30:29.980
Someone told them
about our Lerner rendezvous.

1125
01:30:30.105 --> 01:30:33.150
Someone even killed
poor Billy Bedlam.

1126
01:30:33.275 --> 01:30:38.238
Now, could this all
be coincidence? Perhaps.

1127
01:30:38.322 --> 01:30:42.117
Then someone went
and tied a rope to our plane.

1128
01:30:42.201 --> 01:30:46.664
So, I ask you,
what is going on?

1129
01:30:46.789 --> 01:30:51.627
And I answer.
We have a traitor in our midst.

1130
01:30:51.710 --> 01:30:55.756
Now, how do we flush
a traitor?

1131
01:30:55.839 --> 01:30:58.476
I don't know,
but at the count of three...

1132
01:30:58.601 --> 01:31:01.220
I will find out who is
on my team and who is not.

1133
01:31:01.303 --> 01:31:03.355
That would be one, two...

1134
01:31:03.439 --> 01:31:06.410
Wait! It was me.

1135
01:31:07.309 --> 01:31:09.019
It was me.

1136
01:31:09.144 --> 01:31:13.148
Don't listen to him, man.
T-t-the insulin made him crazy.

1137
01:31:13.232 --> 01:31:16.160
You have been near death
the entire trip?

1138
01:31:16.285 --> 01:31:19.530
- Yeah, motherfucker, it was me.
- No, he's... he's flipped out, man. He's nuts.

1139
01:31:19.655 --> 01:31:21.490
It's pretty clever, huh, bitch?

1140
01:31:21.573 --> 01:31:25.369
- No! Jesus!
- No, that's clever!

1141
01:31:28.672 --> 01:31:32.510
"My daddy is coming home
on July 14th."

1142
01:31:32.835 --> 01:31:36.088
